         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/5/64. ¶ My dear Mr Bentham ¶  ¶ I feel obliged for the interesting communications conveyed in your letter of 25 March, ¶  and am glad to learn that you are making such rapid progress with the Legum...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">64.05.24b</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 146.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Bentham: 'A. [leuco]sperma = suberosa from Glenelg A.[Tumida] one from <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Rockhampton with [a]terete fruit may be A. [leptostachya] If so it <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>has the fs of A [holo]carpa.'</p>
               </note>24/5/64.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Mr Bentham</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I feel obliged for the interesting communications conveyed in your letter of 25 March,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>G. Bentham to M, 25 March 1864 (in this edition as 64-03-25b).</p>
               </note> and am glad to learn that you are making such rapid progress with the <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name> for the Australian flora.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was misled by Lindleys vegetable kingdom<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Lindley (1847). </p>
               </note> when substituting an other name for <name key="Petalostylis">Petalostylis</name>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M believed, on the authority of Lindley (1847), p. 614 that an earlier genus <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Petalostylis">Petalostylis</name>
                     </seg> (Griesebach) already existed, so replaced Robert Brown’s genus by <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Petalogyne </seg>(B56.11.01, p. 324). Lindley had misspelled Griesebach’s '<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Petasostylis</seg>'. M’s action suggests that he had taken Lindley’s book with him on the North Australian Exploring Expedition, 1855-6, because B56.11.01 is part of his letter to W. Hooker, 18 June 1856, written from the Victoria River.</p>
               </note> I enclose a few Leguminous plants received since I last wrote and which are adding a few species or localities to your material.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With Kind regards</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I remain</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <seg style="">Ferd Mueller.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">George Bentham Esq </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>&amp;c </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Petalostylis">Petalostylis</name>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
